laboratory_examinations.findings: Albumin level rose from 26 g/L to 37 g/L, then to 41 g/L.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Increased from 26 g/L (at the start of warfarin therapy) to 37 g/L (6 months later), then to 41 g/L in February 2007.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Platelet count increased from 64 x 10^9 cells/L to 157 x 10^9 cells/L.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Increased from 64 x 10^9 cells/L at diagnosis to 157 x 10^9 cells/L in February 2007.

laboratory_examinations.findings: The second sister's albumin level was 38 g/L.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Increased from 30 g/L (prior to warfarin) to 38 g/L after 6 months of therapy.

laboratory_examinations.findings: The second sister's platelet count was 81 x 10^9 cells/L.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Increased from 54 x 10^9 cells/L (before starting warfarin) to 81 x 10^9 cells/L.

laboratory_examinations.findings: First sister had INRs of 1.4 and 1.3 at different times.
